snippet.title: Pachinko 365 Nichi
snippet.description:
Pachinko 365 Nichi
Developed and published by the Seta Corporation. Seta stands for "Super Entertainment and Total Amusement." Founded in 1985 but unfortunately went under in 2009 when its parent company Aruze decided to disband Seta due to the international financial crisis going on at the time. Seta also developed the Aleck 64, which were arcade cabinets based off the Nintendo 64's hardware. Similarly, Seta co-developed the SSV (Sammy, SETA, Visco) system. Seta manufactured pachinko machine parts and various other electronics throughout the span of its 25 years of business. 
Pachinko 365 Nichi was released in Japan in 1998 for the Nintendo 64.
